OL,3,C'Health emergency' declared by second
OL,4,Ccouncil in north Wales
OL,6,F"The Health Board, in line with other
OL,7,FNHS organisations across the UK, has
OL,8,Fintroduced a Standard Operating
OL,9,FProcedure (SOP) for transferring
OL,10,Fpatients to hospital wards in
OL,11,Fexceptional and extreme circumstances
OL,12,Fonly. This applies to a maximum of two
OL,13,Fpatients per ward, only where a risk
OL,14,Fassessment has deemed it safe to do
OL,15,Fso, and also where overcrowding within
OL,16,Fthe Emergency Department (ED) poses a
OL,17,Fsignificant and immediate risk to
OL,18,Fpatient safety. To date, it has not
OL,19,Fbeen necessary to enact this SOP.
